Kotlin Wrapper Patches for sherpa-onnx v1.12.28
================================================

These patches track our modifications to upstream Kotlin wrapper files in
  android/src/main/kotlin/com/k2fsa/sherpa/onnx/

The upstream files are copied verbatim from:
  https://github.com/k2-fsa/sherpa-onnx (tag v1.12.28)
  android/SherpaOnnx/app/src/main/java/com/k2fsa/sherpa/onnx/

Pinned version: v1.12.28 (setup.sh downloads prebuilt .so at this version)


Files patched
-------------
AudioTagging.patch
  - compute() and external compute() return type: Array<Any> -> Array<AudioEvent>
  - Without this fix, calling compute() would require unsafe Any casts and crash
    at runtime when the JNI bridge returns a typed array.

OfflineRecognizer.patch
  - OfflineRecognizerResult: added durations (TDT model field)
  - OfflineParaformerModelConfig: added qnnConfig
  - OfflineWhisperModelConfig: added enableTokenTimestamps, enableSegmentTimestamps
  - OfflineMoonshineModelConfig: added mergedDecoder
  - OfflineSenseVoiceModelConfig: added qnnConfig
  - Added new data classes: OfflineZipformerCtcModelConfig, OfflineWenetCtcModelConfig,
    OfflineOmnilingualAsrCtcModelConfig, OfflineMedAsrCtcModelConfig,
    OfflineFunAsrNanoModelConfig, OfflineFireRedAsrCtcModelConfig, OfflineCanaryModelConfig
  - OfflineModelConfig: added all new model type fields to match JNI struct layout

Tts.patch
  - OfflineTtsKokoroModelConfig: added lang field
  - OfflineTtsModelConfig: added kitten and pocket fields

OnlineRecognizer.patch
  - OnlineRecognizerResult: added ysProbs field


How to apply on version upgrade
--------------------------------
When setup.sh is updated to a new upstream version:

1. Download the new upstream Kotlin files (same paths as above).
2. Compare each upstream file to our file:
     diff upstream/AudioTagging.kt android/.../AudioTagging.kt
3. Re-apply relevant changes manually, checking for conflicts with new upstream additions.
4. Update the patch files:
     cd <repo-root>
     git diff packages/sherpa-onnx.rn/android/src/main/kotlin/com/k2fsa/sherpa/onnx/AudioTagging.kt \
       > packages/sherpa-onnx.rn/patches/AudioTagging.patch
   (repeat for each file)
5. Update the version header in this README.

To apply a patch from scratch (e.g., against fresh upstream files):
  patch -p1 < patches/AudioTagging.patch

Note: patches are relative to the repo root (git diff output format).
